{
  "texts": [
    "To explore the extent to which sparsity within the network could be increased without impacting accuracy of predictions, we added activity regularization to the loss (L 1 norm on the outputs from ReLU layers, normalized by the volume of the outputs, and scaled by a weighting factor in the global loss).",
    "Experiments Data and training pipelineThe AIS 2024 eye tracking challenge dataset contains 13 subjects, each with 2 to 6 recording sessions [15].",
    "The data is captured with an event camera with resolution of 480 × 640.",
    "The ground truth labels are provided at 100Hz, containing the x and y pixel coordinates of the pupil, and whether the eye is closed.The evaluation on the test set via the Kaggle API is performed at 20Hz.",
    "The test metric is the percentage of correct predictions within 10 pixels of the ground truth labels, in the spatially downsampled space of 60 × 80."
  ]
}